│ Builder.SetInsertPoint(PHParent->getFirstNonPHI());\n        │
│ }\n```\n\n### 5. Conclusion ###\n\nThe proposed change       │
│ corrects the logic for placing instructions that construct   │
│ incoming values for vectorized PHI nodes. By setting the     │
│ insertion point to the terminator of the predecessor block,  │
│ we ensure that the definitions of these values dominate      │
│ their use in the PHI node, resolving the verifier error.     │
│ This fix makes the `slp-vectorizer` more robust when dealing │
│ with vectorization across basic blocks, particularly in the  │
│ presence of loops and complex control flow."})               │
